== Conservation Status

Since 2020, the Pallas's cat has been listed as Least Concern on the IUCN Red List, but their populations are declining due to habitat loss, hunting, and climate change. Conservation efforts are underway to protect their habitats and raise awareness about this unique species.

== Habitat 

Pallas's cats are found in a range of habitats, including grasslands, shrublands, and rocky outcrops. They are distributed across several countries in Central Asia, including Mongolia, China, Kazakhstan, and parts of Russia. Their preference for remote and rugged terrain makes them difficult to study, contributing to the limited knowledge about their ecology and behavior.

